Sports kits will be supplied to all schools in the district within a month , Collector Ch. Vijayamohan said on Wednesday.Inaugurating kho-kho and athletics competitions being organised at the Kurnool outdoor stadium here, the Collector reiterated that education and sports were equally important for children and students must improve their physical fitness and mental acumen by pursuing sports activities. Speaking on the occasion, Kurnool MLA S.V. Mohan Reddy welcomed the governmentâ€™s decision to conduct rangoli and cookery competitions for women as part of Sankranti Sambaralu. He promised to strive for increase in the reservation for sportspersons to five per cent by raising the demand in the Assembly. Meanwhile, the Collector and MLA inspected the multi-purpose indoor stadium and rooms being built on the stadium premises. He directed Executive Engineer (housing) Venkatasubbaiah to complete the works as scheduled by March 31 and warned that a fine of Rs. 5 lakh would be imposed if the works remained incomplete by then.